==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bromidic
<hw>Bro*mid"ic</hw> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or
pertaining to bromide (definition 2).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>conventional or trite; repeated too often;
overfamiliar through overuse -- of sayings, assertions, or discourses;
<as>as, <ex>bromidic</ex> sermons</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> commonplace, hackneyed, shopworn, threadbare,
timeworn, tired, trite, well-worn.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bromidiom</ent>⟦br⟧
